# Phase-3 control-plane synthesizability gate (yosys, generic; no FPGA part).
#
# Reads the design WITHOUT sfu_engine.sv / blocking_helper_engine.sv (those
# black-boxed via blackbox_stubs.v at the top of the yosys -p command). Runs
# the lightweight synthesis pipeline that proves elaboration + procedural
# decode + structural sanity, but skips ABC tech-mapping (which is slow on
# the unmapped 4MB SRAM cell arrays and yields vendor-specific gates that
# aren't useful at this stage — `synth-check-full` will do the area pass
# once BRAM mapping is in place).
#
# Returns 0 iff the control plane is synthesizable.

hierarchy -check -top taccel_top

# Convert procedural -> RTLIL (this is where non-synth constructs fail).
proc

# Structural simplification (flatten then optimize) — keeps the design
# compact without ABC. Use `opt -fast` to skip the most expensive passes.
flatten
opt -fast

# Structural sanity: no combinational loops, no multi-drivers, etc.
check -assert

# Generic cell/area summary (pre-tech-mapping; vendor-independent).
stat
